It's time to give the bedroom a complete renovation. It's the last room in the house that was only given a simple decoration.
Remove the ugly electric fireplace and the stove. Seal the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and repaint. Customize a wardrobe.
We usually start by drawing a rough pencil sketch...
The chaotic phase has passed.
Several dead birds were found behind the chimney, and their bodies were completely dried out :(.
Get ready for the plasterer next week.
Very satisfied with the small alcove next to it.
Put the new wardrobe here (we haven't even started designing it yet🙈)
Ha ha, look what we found behind the radiator!
Remember the addition of the cute little vents to prevent the chimney from getting damp.
Sweep has installed both the chimney cover and the chimney cap. The magpies that like to nest in chimneys should be safer now 🪺
The plasterer has finished. We'll lay the floor tomorrow!
The cork pads have already been laid down, and a roll of toilet paper was even used as an attachment for the vacuum cleaner to suck up sawdust. 😂
Part of the floor is already prepared and ready to be laid. Let's have a cup of tea and rest a bit first.
Well, today's progress has been a bit slow because I had to cut around the door frame to ensure a seamless connection with the hallway (which is also getting its floor installed), and that's quite laborious. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me all along.
Finally finished, but it's all messed up! Even worse, the instructions for assembling the new bed were terrible. Finally, I can have a good night's sleep tonight!
The hallway floor and baseboards are still not done. The renovation workers won't come back for a month, so we can only make do for now. The room is now just bare drywall.
In the evening, I did a simple DIY job, cutting off part of the bottom of the door frame with a saw and chisel, so that the floor could be perfectly laid underneath.
The cork underlayment in the corridor is also installed.
We also finished laying the floor in the corridor yesterday! This morning, we got up at 5 a.m. and went to Heathrow Airport to pick up Package 1, then took a nap. Now we can finally start installing the baseboards in the corridor. We'll fill the gaps after the adhesive dries.
